text.__SUMMARY__: Odostomia sulcosa is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Description: The shell has a length of 2.5 mm.
text.Distribution:
This species occurs in the following locations:
Caribbean Sea
Cuba
Northwest Atlantic
text.Notes:
Additional information regarding this species:
Distribution: Off Georges Bank and Martha's Vineyard
